      <abstract>
        <p>Alfie Kohn humorous letter on June 28 article on College Board overhaul of SAT</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''College Board Announces an Overhaul for the SAT'' (news article, June 28):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''College Board Announces an Overhaul for the SAT'' (news article, June 28):</p>
        <p>Revising is to SAT as</p>
        <p>(a) reformulating is to Coke</p>
        <p>(b) repackaging is to Betamax</p>
        <p>(c) renaming is to Philip Morris</p>
        <p>(d) repainting is to Pinto.</p>
        <p>ALFIE KOHN  Belmont, Mass., June 28, 2002</p>
      </block>
